Subject: [PATCH 45/56] Add missing visitor funcs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds comprehensive support for new AST nodes related to advanced type const[5D[K
constraints, including `TraitRequirementDecl` and `CXXMGConditionalMemberDe[25D[K
`CXXMGConditionalMemberDecl`.

Updates Sema code completion logic and enhances cursor utilities (CXType/CI[10D[K
(CXType/CIndex) to correctly recognize these constructs. This ensures libcl[5D[K
libclang tooling can accurately traverse and understand modern C++ syntax i[1D[K
involving traits and requirements.

diff --git a/clang/lib/Sema/SemaCodeComplete.cpp b/clang/lib/Sema/SemaCodeComplete.cpp
index c8177e027a3a..862fa75f6af0 100644
--- a/clang/lib/Sema/SemaCodeComplete.cpp
+++ b/clang/lib/Sema/SemaCodeComplete.cpp
@@ -4409,6 +4409,9 @@ CXCursorKind clang::getCursorKindForDecl(const Decl *D) {
     return CXCursor_EnumConstantDecl;
   case Decl::Field:
     return CXCursor_FieldDecl;
+  case Decl::TraitRequirement:
+  case Decl::CXXMGConditionalMember:
+    return CXCursor_UnexposedDecl;
   case Decl::Function:
     return CXCursor_FunctionDecl;
   case Decl::ObjCCategory:
diff --git a/clang/tools/libclang/CIndex.cpp b/clang/tools/libclang/CIndex.cpp
